<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddc884ebc-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee" identifier="/us/usc/t2/s145"><num value="145">§ 145.</num><heading> Copies of journals and documents</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Two copies of the journals and documents, and of each book printed by either House of Congress, well bound in calf, shall be deposited in the Library, and must not be taken therefrom.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddc884ebd-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">(R.S. § 97.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="iddc884ebe-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="iddc884ebf-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="iddc884ec0-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">R.S. § 97 derived from Res. <date date="1857-01-02">Jan. 2, 1857</date>, No. 5, § 5, <ref href="/us/stat/11/253">11 Stat. 253</ref>.</p>
</note>
